{{Infobox journal | title = Environmental Development | cover = | editor = Eleanor Milne | discipline = [[Environmental science]], [[environmental policy]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Environ. Dev. | publisher = [[Elsevier]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 2012-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.journals.elsevier.com/environmental-development | link2 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/22114645 | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 778327918 | LCCN = 2015205288 | CODEN = | ISSN = 2211-4645 | eISSN = }} '''''Environmental Development''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[environmental science]] and [[environmental policy|policy]] published by [[Elsevier]]. In January 2018, Natarajan Ishwaran became the new [[editor-in-chief]]. He succeeded Eleanor Milne ([[Colorado State University]], now Subject Editor for Climate Change) EIC from July 2015. The founding editor was Theo Beckers ([[Tilburg University]]).<ref name=SCOPE>{{cite web |url=http://www.scopenvironment.org/ |title=Scientific Committee on Problems of the Environment |work=Homepage |accessdate=9 October 2016}}</ref>
The journal is associated with the [[Scientific Committee on Problems of the Environment]] (SCOPE)<ref name=SCOPE/> and is abstracted and indexed in the [[Emerging Sources Citation Index]]<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2016-10-09}}</ref> and [[Scopus]].<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |title=Content overview |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus |accessdate=2016-10-09}}</ref>
