{{Infobox Magazine| title = Museum Management and Curatorship | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | editor = Robert R. Janes | frequency = [[Quarterly]] | circulation = | category = [[Museology]] | company = [[Taylor & Francis]] | firstdate = 1986 | country = [[UK]] | language = [[English language|English]] | website = [http://www.tandf.co.uk/journals/titles/09647775.asp tandf.co.uk] | issn = 0964-7775 | }}
'''''Museum Management and Curatorship''''' ('''MMC''') is an international peer-reviewed, journal aimed at [[museum]] professionals, consultants, educators, and researchers. Its content is intended to examine current issues in museum practice. The journal covers aspects such as [[Administration (business)|administration]], [[archives]], [[collections management]], [[communications]], [[habitat conservation|conservation]], [[Multiculturalism|diversity]], [[globalization]], [[governance]], interpretation, [[leadership]], [[management]], [[new technology]], [[professional ethics]], [[community service|public service]], purpose/mission, and [[social responsibility]].
The journal is published quarterly by [[Routledge]].
