{{about|a 1968 test flight|the carrier rocket|Soyuz-2|the mission identified by NASA as ISS Soyuz 2|Soyuz TM-32}} {{Infobox spaceflight | name = Soyuz 2 | image = | image_caption = | insignia = | mission_type = Test flight | operator = [[Soviet space program]] | COSPAR_ID = 1968-093A | SATCAT = 3511 | mission_duration = | distance_travelled = | orbits_completed = 48 | spacecraft = | spacecraft_type = [[Soyuz 7K-OK]] | manufacturer = Experimental Design Bureau [[OKB-1]] | launch_mass = {{convert|6450|kg|lb}} | landing_mass = | launch_date = {{start-date|October 25, 1968, 09:00|timezone=yes}}&nbsp;UTC | launch_rocket = [[Soyuz (rocket)|Soyuz]] | launch_site = [[Baikonur Cosmodrome|Baikonur]] [[Baikonur Cosmodrome Site 1|1/5]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.astronautix.com/sites/baiurlc1.htm |title=Baikonur LC1 |accessdate=2009-03-04 |publisher=Encyclopedia Astronautica |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090415160730/http://www.astronautix.com/sites/baiurlc1.htm |archivedate=2009-04-15 |df= }}</ref> | landing_date = {{end-date|October 28, 1968, 07:51|timezone=yes}}&nbsp;UTC; | landing_site = | orbit_epoch = | orbit_reference = [[Geocentric orbit|Geocentric]] | orbit_regime = [[Low Earth orbit|Low Earth]] | orbit_periapsis = {{convert|191|km|mi}} | orbit_apoapsis = {{convert|229|km|mi}} | orbit_inclination = 51.70&nbsp;degrees | orbit_period = 88.60&nbsp;minutes | apsis = gee }}
'''Soyuz 2''' ({{lang-ru|'''Союз 2'''}}, '''Union 2''') was an uncrewed [[spacecraft]] in the [[Soyuz spacecraft|Soyuz]] family intended to be the target of a docking maneuver by the manned [[Soyuz 3]] spacecraft. It was intended to be the first docking of a manned spacecraft in the Soviet space program. Although the two craft approached closely, the docking did not take place and the first successful Soviet docking of manned spacecraft took place in the joint [[Soyuz 4]] and [[Soyuz 5]] mission.
==Mission parameters== *'''Mass:''' {{convert|6450|kg|lb|abbr=on}} *'''Perigee:''' {{convert|191|km|mi|abbr=on}} *'''Apogee:''' {{convert|229|km|mi|abbr=on}} *'''Inclination:''' 51.70° *'''Period:''' 88.60 min
